; c64asm listing  (origin $0801, 60 bytes)
; CYCLES column: a plain number is a fixed cycle count; "b/b+1" means b cycles, +1 more if this instruction's indexed addressing crosses a page boundary; "2/3/4" means a branch's usual 2 (not taken) / 3 (taken) / 4 (taken, crossing a page). Blank means an illegal/undocumented opcode (.cpu 6510x) -- see c64asm-reference.md "Listing file format".

ADDR  BYTES      CYCLES  SOURCE
080D  A2 00      2               ldx #$00
080F  BD 30 08   4/5             lda message,x
0812  F0 07      2/3/4           beq done_print
0814  20 D2 FF   6               jsr CHROUT
0817  E8         2               inx
0818  4C 0F 08   3               jmp print_loop
081B  A9 00      2               lda #BLACK
081D  8D 20 D0   4               sta BORDER
0820  EE 20 D0   6               inc BORDER
0823  A2 00      2               ldx #$00
0825  A0 00      2               ldy #$00
0827  C8         2               iny
0828  D0 FD      2/3/4           bne delay_inner
082A  CA         2               dex
082B  D0 F8      2/3/4           bne delay_outer
082D  4C 20 08   3               jmp color_loop

Symbol table:
  BLACK                = $0000
  BORDER               = $D020
  CHROUT               = $FFD2
  color_loop           = $0820
  delay_inner          = $0827
  delay_outer          = $0825
  done_print           = $081B
